how do you cope after the death of your baby our son died when i was months prgnant from kidney failure i'm having a hard time coping this is the second baby we've lost we are afraid to try again any advise our daughter died when i was months pregnant because she had a defective heart oh man i know what you're feeling you didn't mention the cause of your first miscarriage so i'm assuming they're not related all i can tell you is that women have multiple miscarriages sometimes and go on to have healthy pregnancies and babies first you need to take time and grieve it took months before i felt normal again and like i could try not before fully grieving first write your son a letter tell him how you feel thank him for blessing your life for such a short time say goodbye most important remember that saying goodbye doesn't mean you forget him you let go of the pregnancy but the baby will stay in your heart forever and when you're ready you try again take care and god bless Pregnancy Miscarriage Abortion Obstetrics EastEnders Abortion debate Stillbirth Virgin Mary in Islam Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Jon Secada Charmed Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Folic acid Hollyoaks Mary, the mother of Jesus Grief Friends Religion and abortion Cliff Richard Prenatal diagnosis Turner syndrome One Tree Hill (TV series) Sex and the City Breastfeeding Urinary incontinence Jacob Anne Boleyn John the Baptist Pitaten Kodocha Frankie Laine Henry VIII of England Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Spina bifida Intact dilation and extraction Coeliac disease Prostate cancer Melanie Wilkes The Beatles discography Lucille Ball Premature birth In vitro fertilisation Humphrey Bogart Days of our Lives Theory of conduct History of As the World Turns (2000-present) James I of England Childbirth Marilyn Monroe Phoebe Halliwell Social rule One Life to Live Knots Landing Cephalic disorder Psoriasis Amy Dumas Midwifery Jacques-Louis David Search for Tomorrow Tocopherol Night (book) Diethylsti